# Pull table for county calls for Henrico County
call_table = pd.read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/martindavid1995/Datasets/master/Open_View_-_Henrico_County_Calls_for_Service.csv")
# Get the noise complaints/parties
noise_complaints = call_table.loc[call_table["Final_Call_Type"]=='Loud Party Or Noise']
# Reduce data down to Three-Chopt district to thin down dataset
noise_complaints = noise_complaints.loc[noise_complaints["Magisterial_District"]=='Three-Chopt']
# Reset indices
df = noise_complaints.reset_index(drop=True)
df

# Gather a list of days that would be considered weekends. Just using Saturday and Sunday wouldn't be accurate as parties can 
# start on fridays and can also go into monday mornings, so we must account for that. 
isWeekend = []
for index, row in df.iterrows():
    if row["Weekday"] == "SAT" or row["Weekday"] == "SUN":
        isWeekend.append(True)
#   Fridays are considered weekend parties if they are after 6PM
    elif row["Weekday"] == "FRI" and row["Hour"] >= 18:
        isWeekend.append(True)
#   Mondays are considered weekend parties if they are before 6AM
    elif row["Weekday"] == "MON" and row["Hour"] <= 6:
        isWeekend.append(True)
    else:
        isWeekend.append(False)   

# Add isWeekend column to DataFrame
df["Weekend"] = isWeekend

# Center the map in the Three-Chopt district
map_osm = folium.Map(location=[37.65287899832559, -77.5929329348909], zoom_start=11.5)

for index, row in df.iterrows():
#   There is one weird outlier along the river to the SE - this removes it from the map
    if row["Longitude"] == df["Longitude"].max():
        continue
#   Mark weekends as red
    if row["Weekend"] == True:
        folium.Marker(location=[row["Latitude"], row["Longitude"]], icon=folium.Icon(color='darkred')).add_to(map_osm)
#   Mark weekdays as blue
    if row["Weekend"] == False:
        folium.Marker(location=[row["Latitude"], row["Longitude"]], icon=folium.Icon(color='lightblue')).add_to(map_osm)

map_osm
